         <abstract>
            <p>Changes in the general level of stock prices are strongly correlated with current and future changes in the money supply, rather than past changes, as money supply watchers have been led to expect. Thus, although money matters, it is futile to attempt to predict stock price movements with money supply data.</p>
          </abstract>
